http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Sun-viewing-and-stargazing/article13979973.ece

Visitors to the Pride of India exhibition are being treated to a view of the sun in all its glory, including the black spots. The Indian Institute of Geomagnetism has installed a dedicated sun telescope for the public. Located at the entrance of the exhibition, it is popular with the visitors. Meanwhile, the Karnataka Science and Technology Promotion Society will conduct stargazing programmes during the expo. It has two dedicated telescopes and there will be three sessions in which about 100 people can participate.